[[Image:Yermo0301_040.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Alex Yermolinsky at the 2003 U.S. Chess Championships in Seattle, Washington]]

'''Alex "Yermo" Yermolinsky''' (born [[April 11]] [[1958]] in the former [[Soviet Union]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[chess]] [[International Grandmaster|Grandmaster]]. In [[1993]], Alex won the [[U.S. Chess Championship]], a title he shared with [[Alexander Shabalov]]. In 1996 he was the sole champion of the United States.

